1
00:00:57,682 --> 00:00:59,267
BEST OUTFIELDER
KANG JONG-RYEOL

2
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:01,978
Golden Glove winner? MVP?

3
00:01:02,395 --> 00:01:05,982
I was chosen as the youngest player
to win those awards.

4
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:16,451
You see,

5
00:01:16,951 --> 00:01:21,664
having the world in the palm of my hands
so easily

6
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:25,710
made life seem too easy.

7
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:30,632
I thought that life
just went by easily like that.

8
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:34,511
Is one bill a day
enough allowance for an eight-year-old?

9
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,097
I'm not up to date on the market price.

10
00:01:37,555 --> 00:01:40,391
I thought that kids
basically raised themselves.

11
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:43,186
How am I going to introduce you?

12
00:01:43,394 --> 00:01:45,396
It'll be troublesome
if a scandal breaks out.

13
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:47,899
I figured

14
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,152
that people would always
stay by your side.

15
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:56,616
It's the same with marriage.

16
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:59,452
I didn't think marriage needed any work.

17
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:03,123
But getting punched in the face

18
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,210
woke me up.

19
00:02:09,838 --> 00:02:13,091
Did you just punch my nose?

20
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:15,635
Fight with everything you have.

21
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:18,096
It turns out that

22
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,141
I've never fought for something

23
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,769
with everything I have.

24
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,814
It must be why

25
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,526
your dad's being punished.

26
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:48,001
He must be happy to be home, too.

27
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:50,628
After polishing off two portions,
he conked out.

28
00:02:53,214 --> 00:02:54,465
He asked me

29
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:58,136
to wake him up at 6 a.m.
so that he can go to Jun-gi's.

30
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:01,472
Did he brush his teeth?

31
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:06,477
Of course. I can help him do that,

32
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:09,981
so you can stay out longer if you'd like.

33
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:11,900
What's this?

34
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,777
Gosh, you've become
a shopaholic these days.

35
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:19,282
Dongbaek, you can always stay the night

36
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:21,284
at sauna's if you want.

37
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:22,952
Joker was caught,

38
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:27,707
so you two can enjoy
some time alone as a reward.

39
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,001
Mom, Yong-sik and I broke up,

40
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,756
so enough with the nonsense.

41
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:37,800
Wait.

42
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:41,512
Did he break up with you?

43
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:43,806
Were you dumped?

44
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:45,850
I dumped him.

45
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:48,937
Why? Who are you to do that?

46
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,940
You two idiots
just broke it off like that?

47
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:54,525
Yes, just like that.

48
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:58,154
You know, it was simple.

49
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:00,740
There was no fuss.

50
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,785
We just quietly broke it off.

51
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:12,627
Well,

52
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:15,922
I know we broke up,

53
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:19,217
but I still couldn't let you

54
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,636
walk home alone.

55
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:24,973
There's no need to keep being a gentleman.

56
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,101
You should get going.

57
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:29,727
Right, then...

58
00:04:33,314 --> 00:04:34,357
I'll get going.

59
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,236
I'm going.

60
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:53,126
What? Why are you back?

61
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:54,252
Dongbaek,

62
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:56,296
you see...

63
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:57,880
Well...

64
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:01,301
Call me if there's any trouble.

65
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,636
I'm always on your side.

66
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,681
Why would you say that?

67
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:09,100
Why would you be on my side anyway?

68
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:12,520
Joker was caught now,

69
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:14,689
so you...

70
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:17,650
You know,

71
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,737
live your life like you used to.

72
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:24,657
Shouldn't you tell me to be happy?

73
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:27,201
Why would I tell you that?

74
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:31,998
Even though I don't wish you happiness,

75
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:37,628
I know for a fact
that you'll be happy

76
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,965
since you are

77
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,470
awesome and beautiful.

78
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:56,022
Whatever you used to tell me

79
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:58,524
felt like

80
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:02,403
a good luck charm to me.

81
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,909
Because you encouraged me,

82
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,286
my life...

83
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:13,664
changed for real.

84
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,963
Thank you so much for everything.

85
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:30,765
Well,

86
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:33,101
you know...

87
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:36,938
It's...

88
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:40,691
really over, right?

89
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:48,074
I never had an amicable ending
with you and Jong-ryeol,

90
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:51,160
so I never knew that a goodbye existed.

91
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,666
Truth be told, it's more annoying.

92
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,335
He's too much of a catch.

93
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:02,422
Are you planning to stay single
your whole life?

94
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:05,842
You know, once in the past...

95
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:09,470
Maybe I was possessed or something.

96
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:13,307
Anyway, life was so exhausting

97
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:16,936
that I looked up how painful suicide

98
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:19,856
-by carbon monoxide poisoning was.
-What on earth?

99
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:23,860
I only looked it up.

100
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,612
Just then, Pil-gu suddenly

101
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:29,615
called for me.

102
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:34,412
It was the first time he said "Mom."

103
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,416
Oddly enough,

104
00:07:40,334 --> 00:07:43,796
that single word took me from hell
and placed me in heaven.

105
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:49,760
He is a deity to me.

106
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:55,391
So I'm fine giving him my all
in this life.

107
00:07:57,852 --> 00:07:58,853
Dongbaek,

108
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:00,980
you'll get lonely.

109
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:04,066
And loneliness can kill you.

110
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,902
As if I have the time for that.

111
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:15,077
CAMELLIA

112
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,497
Who gets over a breakup by making kimchi?

113
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:20,416
I may be crying inside,
but my hands are busy.

114
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:23,586
Mom, can you bring the radishes now?

115
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:28,549
Stay busy to confuse your mind.

116
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:35,389
Just like people do in TV series,
I'd like to let sadness take over me.

117
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:37,558
ONGSAN WATER AUTHORITY

118
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,936
Fictional breakups you see on TV?

119
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,896
Mister. Sir!

120
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,773
It's only a fantasy.

121
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:46,526
Where do you live, sir?

122
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,236
One stir-fried pork coming up!

123
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:51,822
The heartbreak might pull me down,

124
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,991
but my rent makes me get back up.

125
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:02,458
My ruthless and repetitive daily routine

126
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:05,044
keeps me sane.

127
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:16,514
You know,
Joker could very well be shorter than me.

128
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:20,268
I'm sure you're aware of the type.

129
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,604
He's just like a man
you'd see on the street.

130
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:25,565
Just an ordinary man.

131
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:38,995
Why did you insist on
going on the delivery run?

132
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:42,999
Why did you?

133
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:47,753
I can easily ride the scooter, too.

134
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:52,216
CAMELLIA

135
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,010
Gosh, this is awesome!

136
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:55,886
This is so much fun!

137
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,523
-Wait, how should I go back?
-Dongbaek!

138
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:09,191
Dongbaek!

139
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:11,402
-Dongbaek.
-Hyang-mi?

140
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:16,282
I see you can ride it now.

141
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,868
Are you aware
that you passed two bus stops?

142
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:21,704
I saw you from the intersection up there,

143
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,581
but you kept on riding this.

144
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:28,377
So did you follow me
all the way here on foot?

145
00:10:28,669 --> 00:10:31,088
You're not so much of a klutz
like you think you are.

146
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:35,760
I can't believe you followed me, though.
You should've just stayed there.

147
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,928
I was worried you'd fall.

148
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:43,893
Why did you have to
go on the delivery run that day?

149
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,738
How am I supposed to live without you?

150
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:06,832
You should've rather stolen my money
and lived somewhere happily ever after.

151
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,629
Why did you come back?

152
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,346
LOVE MEMORIAL HALL

153
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:23,474
Mom, for some reason,

154
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:26,811
I feel like Hyang-mi's still alive.

155
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:31,649
You have to let her go
so that she can rest in peace.

156
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:37,113
Here.

157
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:47,373
Don't you even dream
about resting in peace in heaven.

158
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:53,963
If you die too,
I'll be grieving back to back.

159
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:56,424
You'll be killing me.

160
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:01,804
My head hurts more than my kidney
these days because of you.

161
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,975
Hyang-mi's gone now

162
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,936
and I even broke up with Yong-sik.

163
00:12:09,019 --> 00:12:11,480
So can't you please stay by my side?

164
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:15,025
Let me tell you this again.
You're not giving me your kidney.

165
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:19,155
And let me tell you this.
You're not dying.

166
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,073
Live and pay off your debt.

167
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,868
How's that paying it off?
I'll just be in your debt forever.

168
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:25,286
Mom.

169
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:26,412
7 YEARS AND 3 MONTHS OF MOTHERHOOD

170
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:27,371
Mom.

171
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:31,500
I'm only asking because I'm upset,
but can we hold hands?

172
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,044
Did we never do this before?

173
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:37,631
You're a weird one, you know.

174
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:40,384
How can you even be fond of me?

175
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:44,472
I don't know. I just like calling you Mom.

176
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,558
So stop fighting me on this
and stay by my side.

177
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:56,233
Ms. Hong?

178
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,486
CAMELLIA

179
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:04,241
Aren't you open today?

180
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:11,832
I only ordered stir-fried pork.

181
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:16,629
Everyone thinks that customers rule,

182
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:18,547
but this is actually my kingdom.

183
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:21,133
I serve whatever I want.

184
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,845
That's why you never gave Gyu-tae
any peanuts?

185
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:26,806
Not even once.

186
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:29,433
I never gave him any.

187
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,688
How do you even laugh like that?

188
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:37,733
That smile you have...

189
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:40,778
is quite intimidating.

190
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:46,575
Do I intimidate you?

191
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:54,667
Some think that you can never be happy.

192
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:59,672
They find comfort
in saying how bad they feel for you.

193
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:01,882
But you smile quite easily.

194
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,468
And it's a pretty smile, too.

195
00:14:05,469 --> 00:14:07,263
No wonder it's annoying.

196
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,265
Of course I'm intimidated.

197
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:15,271
Anyway, you should keep laughing.

198
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:19,608
Show everyone how happy you are.

199
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:22,736
Well,

200
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:27,616
I gave up on being openly happy
a long time ago.

201
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,326
Why is that?

202
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:34,957
What people think of me is their problem.

203
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:41,964
I used to think of happiness
as something like a test score.

204
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:47,511
I used to look up
at the scoreboard others made

205
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:50,973
and thought about where I stand.

206
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,684
No matter how hard I looked up though,

207
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,728
I couldn't find an answer.

208
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:59,148
So why would I stick around
looking for one?

209
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,526
I dismissed their scoreboard
as their own game

210
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:05,779
and scored my own life
based on my standards.

211
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:10,576
Being happy by my own standards
is all I need in life, right?

212
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:19,251
It seems like your heart
has its own flowerbed.

213
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:25,257
Meanwhile, I aced the SAT,
went to a prestigious law school,

214
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,427
but no flowers bloomed within me.

215
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:37,353
Could I bring a glass of my own?

216
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:40,064
Dongbaek,

217
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:43,442
is there any hard liquor
that Gyu-tae keeps here?

218
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:46,111
What was the brand again?

219
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,529
Ja-yeong, gosh.

220
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:50,032
How am I supposed to carry her home?

221
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:52,618
I've never been able to do that.

222
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:56,705
What should I have done then?
I couldn't let Ja-yeong stay here.

223
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,290
You're using her name?

224
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:04,213
It only took you a night
to become friends with her

225
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:07,591
when you're still formal to me
after all this time?

226
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:09,969
This is inverse discrimination.

227
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,929
It's reverse discrimination.

228
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,306
Anyway, enough with the nonsense.

229
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:19,311
Just so you know,
I told Ja-yeong everything.

230
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:21,897
About what?

231
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:26,276
About me? You put in a good word for me?

232
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:28,612
Not that.

233
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:30,864
I told her about Hyang-mi.

234
00:16:32,741 --> 00:16:36,120
I said that Hyang-mi
isn't some man-eater or a slut.

235
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:39,164
Darn.

236
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,084
Isn't there

237
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:45,254
an adjustment period
for couples going through a divorce?

238
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:47,715
She hasn't dumped you yet.

239
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:51,760
Come by with Ja-yeong sometime
and I will...

240
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:55,431
serve the peanut dish

241
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:57,307
for free

242
00:16:58,225 --> 00:16:59,351
in your name.

243
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:03,689
Dongbaek...

244
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:06,066
What now?

245
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:10,070
Are you crying? Gosh.

246
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:19,955
How about a yearly rent from now on?

247
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:24,626
Do you have the money? Want a loan, too?

248
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:28,130
Let's go.

249
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,134
What?

250
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:34,845
What do you mean?

251
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:36,847
Online? What about it?

252
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:46,023
Jessica...

253
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:47,900
topped Joker.

254
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,652
POPULAR REAL-TIME KEYWORDS

255
00:17:52,654 --> 00:17:54,823
KANG JONG-RYEOL'S WIFE WAS MARRIED BEFORE?

256
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:56,784
WHY DID JESSICA LIE?

257
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:08,128
The police promised
to reveal every crime he committed,

258
00:18:08,212 --> 00:18:10,130
but they're just waiting for a confession.

259
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,674
Yes, that's the reality of it.

260
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,968
What still seems to be the issue

261
00:18:15,552 --> 00:18:20,140
is the psychological evaluation
the defense

262
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:22,101
-handed in.
-Are you kidding me?

263
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:26,522
Unbelievable. Not that defense again.

264
00:18:29,066 --> 00:18:30,484
This feels wrong.

265
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:31,819
Why?

266
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:35,614
Are you worried that he'll get a lesser
sentence due to his mental illness?

267
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:37,157
No, that's not it.

268
00:18:38,742 --> 00:18:40,911
Is Heung-sik really moving?

269
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:48,293
Are you really moving?

270
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:53,590
Who will ask me over
to repair anything anymore?

271
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:58,387
Your father's to blame, not you.

272
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:05,602
Still,

273
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:08,772
I'm just as guilty.

274
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:12,151
I knew his legs were better

275
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:14,111
and I knew

276
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,197
he was poisoning the cat food.

277
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,367
Aren't you an avid cat-lover?

278
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:22,744
Why did you let him do that?

279
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:26,248
My dad hates loud noises.

280
00:19:27,374 --> 00:19:29,501
He took it out on the cats

281
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,504
when they cried at night.

282
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:37,384
He just couldn't control himself.

283
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:40,012
Damn it.

284
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:47,644
You lived here your whole life,
so where will you go?

285
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,151
My dad even forgot to take his glasses.

286
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:58,488
Is this really the time
to worry about that?

287
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:00,908
I hate him, too.

288
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:04,703
But what can I do?

289
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:06,580
He's still my dad.

290
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,293
He may be a killer,

291
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:15,047
but he's still my dad.

292
00:20:17,925 --> 00:20:19,593
Damn it.

293
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:25,432
Here. Stop fidgeting with it
and hand it over.

294
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:30,562
Damn it.

295
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:39,321
Why do you keep following me?

296
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:42,032
You see your doctor on
Tuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.

297
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:44,618
-I'm not blind, you know.
-So what?

298
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:48,664
You're going to watch me get my dialysis?

299
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:51,208
I'm allowed to have privacy, you know.

300
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:54,753
I have the right
to keep certain things hidden.

301
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:59,007
I heard that dialysis can be tough.

302
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:01,051
A transplant is the best.

303
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:03,637
Dongbaek, whether I die or not,

304
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:07,474
I have the right to choose my own fate!
Don't be like this!

305
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:09,935
No, you don't have the right to die.

306
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:11,270
Why not?

307
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:14,106
You've been my mom
for only seven years and three months.

308
00:21:17,025 --> 00:21:17,901
What?

309
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:21,947
Do you even know
how long we've lived together?

310
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:27,160
Seven years when I was young
and three months just this year.

311
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:30,038
That's it.

312
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,040
That's not how mothers should be.

313
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,043
You were a short-term mom

314
00:21:36,044 --> 00:21:38,672
and now you want me to just
live off your insurance money?

315
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:43,593
Mom,

316
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:46,305
have you ever been an orphan?

317
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:50,475
You've been constantly in my life.

318
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:52,728
Every day, your presence hurt me.

319
00:21:59,151 --> 00:22:03,155
I'm too annoyed and pissed off to let you
off the hook with the insurance money.

320
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:07,659
I must live with you for 20 more years.

321
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:10,037
So stay alive

322
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:11,913
and pay off your debt.

323
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:15,167
Be a mother!

324
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:21,173
Darn her.

325
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:24,092
She won't even let me die
on my own accord.

326
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:32,851
She needs to keep her appointments.

327
00:22:32,934 --> 00:22:37,522
You know how dangerous it can be
to skip dialysis.

328
00:22:38,815 --> 00:22:40,567
What happens if she misses a session?

329
00:22:42,319 --> 00:22:45,989
Being late for a dialysis
is considered as suicide.

330
00:22:54,122 --> 00:22:56,958
The nurse's aunt
was a day late for her dialysis

331
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:59,211
and she died while playing golf.

332
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,588
Are you gambling on your life?

333
00:23:02,005 --> 00:23:03,840
Do you not care about living?

334
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:06,802
You have no idea how much this hurts.

335
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:12,307
My blood is drained from my body
and swapped with clean blood.

336
00:23:13,934 --> 00:23:15,102
Scary, isn't it?

337
00:23:16,895 --> 00:23:18,063
Does it hurt?

338
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:23,068
It's not that I just feel weak.
I'm in a terrible mood as well.

339
00:23:24,945 --> 00:23:28,698
Do you have any idea how sad it is

340
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:31,785
to know that a machine
is keeping you alive?

341
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:39,876
I'm going to schedule
the surgery with your doctor,

342
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,253
so just know that.

343
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:47,801
Are you scared? Should I stay with you?

344
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:53,932
So...

345
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,936
how was the seven years
and three months for you?

346
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,189
Was it all right?

347
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:06,486
Was it?

348
00:24:10,615 --> 00:24:14,411
You really are the weirdest. Unbelievable.

349
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:19,082
Be strong and hang in there.

350
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:24,004
If you can't live for yourself,
then live for me. Okay?

351
00:24:42,439 --> 00:24:45,567
Go ahead. You like rice with toppings.

352
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:50,322
I'm only asking because I'm curious.

353
00:24:50,906 --> 00:24:52,365
What are you calling a joke?

354
00:24:53,116 --> 00:24:56,453
We can't stop joking around
unless you tell us what you mean by it.

355
00:24:58,413 --> 00:24:59,581
Get me some water.

356
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:06,838
Why can't I meet the suspect
that I caught myself?

357
00:25:06,922 --> 00:25:09,925
Call it a visitation if you want,
I have rights.

358
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:13,053
Actually, you don't.
Mere officers don't get that right.

359
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:15,889
Your job is to keep order on the streets.

360
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:20,769
I'm not here just for kicks.
I have something for him.

361
00:25:21,228 --> 00:25:23,897
-I have a reason to see him.
-And what may that be?

362
00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:29,945
Why can't his son visit him?

363
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,113
You're violating his rights

364
00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:34,324
by depriving a man
to wear his own glasses.

365
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:37,994
We have the right to decide
who gets to visit the suspect.

366
00:25:38,078 --> 00:25:40,622
Right, then I'll also
take the liberty to report this

367
00:25:40,705 --> 00:25:42,624
to the National Human Rights Commission.

368
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,125
I'm sure

369
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:47,504
you're aware that murderers' rights
are more important than yours.

370
00:25:52,926 --> 00:25:54,010
You.

371
00:25:54,594 --> 00:25:58,765
None of the cameras should be on
during my visit.

372
00:25:58,848 --> 00:26:01,643
It all boils down to his human rights.

373
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:04,729
Human rights, sure.
Anyway, you have ten minutes.

374
00:26:12,487 --> 00:26:13,738
Heung-sik's leaving Ongsan.

375
00:26:16,616 --> 00:26:17,993
Why does he have to suffer

376
00:26:19,911 --> 00:26:21,621
when you're the killer?

377
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:28,295
You're the last person I want to see,

378
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:32,465
but I'm here

379
00:26:33,466 --> 00:26:35,051
as a favor to Heung-sik.

380
00:26:37,804 --> 00:26:38,722
I'll get going then.

381
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,684
Are people pointing fingers at him

382
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:45,645
for being a murderer's son?

383
00:26:51,568 --> 00:26:53,069
Heung-sik...

384
00:26:54,696 --> 00:26:56,740
still considers you as a dad
despite all that.

385
00:26:58,325 --> 00:27:00,619
The father tried to frame his son
as an accomplice,

386
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:03,413
but he wants you to have your glasses.

387
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:05,749
He's not my accomplice.

388
00:27:06,499 --> 00:27:08,001
While you sit in here in silence,

389
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:10,920
Heung-sik's personal details
were all made known,

390
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:12,297
and he's already shunned.

391
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:14,841
You should think of him

392
00:27:16,009 --> 00:27:17,135
and pay for your crimes

393
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:19,304
like a father.

394
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:22,599
They were being a joke!

395
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:25,435
They all died because they joked around.

396
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:44,037
You know what?

397
00:27:44,788 --> 00:27:46,456
They're all edited.

398
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:51,628
They're all edited,
and my mom will sue everyone.

399
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:53,254
We'll find a law firm...

400
00:27:59,969 --> 00:28:00,845
What?

401
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,889
Give me your phone.

402
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,308
Stop looking at it for a while.

403
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,482
Don't turn on your computer
or log into your social media.

404
00:28:12,565 --> 00:28:14,526
Don't read the comments of news articles.

405
00:28:21,741 --> 00:28:23,451
You must find me hilarious.

406
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:25,203
You were dying to divorce me,

407
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:27,539
and you have your reason now.

408
00:28:27,872 --> 00:28:31,501
I won't abandon someone who fell down.
Even if I divorce you, it's not now.

409
00:28:35,588 --> 00:28:39,008
You're Ji-seon's mom
and I won't let you look ridiculous.

410
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:42,554
I'll take care of everything,

411
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:45,849
so stop worrying
and don't browse the internet.

412
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:50,520
To be frank,
you two weren't living together anyway.

413
00:28:50,645 --> 00:28:52,188
And it really doesn't concern you.

414
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:55,233
So I shouldn't be concerned?

415
00:28:55,483 --> 00:28:57,402
Since we'll be strangers
after the divorce?

416
00:28:59,946 --> 00:29:03,074
But to be frank,
don't you think we're complete strangers?

417
00:29:03,825 --> 00:29:06,119
I'm not concerned about you
making money with me.

418
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:10,248
Hey.

419
00:29:10,331 --> 00:29:12,876
I mean, sir.

420
00:29:14,043 --> 00:29:17,172
Please remove
all the articles about my wife.

421
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:20,550
If you do that for me,

422
00:29:21,342 --> 00:29:22,594
I'll renew the contract

423
00:29:22,677 --> 00:29:25,013
and do everything
from loan shark ads to any events.

424
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:26,097
But...

425
00:29:27,056 --> 00:29:28,516
if you don't do this for me,

426
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:33,229
I'll just retire.

427
00:29:34,939 --> 00:29:36,524
POWER OFF

428
00:29:43,865 --> 00:29:46,242
But you're at fault, too.

429
00:29:47,869 --> 00:29:49,746
I just told some lies,

430
00:29:50,371 --> 00:29:51,664
but I don't have any kids.

431
00:29:52,248 --> 00:29:56,920
Yes, you're right. I'm at fault.
But let's make one thing clear.

432
00:30:03,593 --> 00:30:04,844
Let's say I knew.

433
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:09,599
I knew that you were once married.

434
00:30:10,642 --> 00:30:13,520
And everyone who needed to know
already knew that.

435
00:30:17,899 --> 00:30:19,901
That means you didn't lie,

436
00:30:20,693 --> 00:30:22,237
and you don't have to feel small.

437
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:24,697
Do you understand?

438
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:31,120
A person shows their true self
at the very last moment.

439
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:36,000
Their true warm self
that was hidden behind their aloofness.

440
00:30:39,504 --> 00:30:42,215
His true cold self
he hid behind his aloofness began to show

441
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:44,342
without a doubt.

442
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:48,179
They're a joke
who can't even unclog their own john.

443
00:30:49,222 --> 00:30:52,767
Some idiots look for us
even when their gas is cut off.

444
00:30:53,893 --> 00:30:56,813
But they show off like they're a big deal,
so I couldn't help it.

445
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:02,318
If it looks like I can kill them,
I need to do that.

446
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:09,701
Is that why you started to kill them?

447
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:11,744
It's only tough to get started.

448
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:15,081
All of you could do it if you wanted to.

449
00:31:23,172 --> 00:31:24,299
Is that why you killed

450
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:26,259
Ms. Kim Song-hwa?

451
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:30,555
That mad bitch

452
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:34,976
joked around with me
when she should be grateful.

453
00:31:35,977 --> 00:31:38,104
That mad bitch
always got stuff delivered to her

454
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:40,189
with the money she got
working as an escort.

455
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:41,149
KIM SONG-HWA

456
00:31:41,232 --> 00:31:44,027
But she always got them
delivered to our store.

457
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:49,490
The delivery guy took 2,500 won from me
saying it's cash on delivery.

458
00:31:51,868 --> 00:31:55,288
And that bitch wouldn't take my change.

459
00:31:55,955 --> 00:31:57,248
She wouldn't take it.

460
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:58,374
500 WON

461
00:31:58,958 --> 00:32:00,710
And the look on her face.

462
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,170
Keep the change.

463
00:32:02,253 --> 00:32:03,630
The look on her face...

464
00:32:05,882 --> 00:32:09,218
I always hear this noise
whenever I lose it.

465
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:12,639
I can't live with that noise, can I?

466
00:32:13,222 --> 00:32:16,726
I can't even bear
to listen to the sound of a clock.

467
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:22,023
VICTIM KIM SEON-SUK, FEMALE IN 50S

468
00:32:25,693 --> 00:32:28,780
That bitch, the co-up head,
was a clean freak.

469
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:30,448
But her toilet always got clogged.

470
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:38,623
I went to unclog her john,

471
00:32:39,248 --> 00:32:41,459
but she wouldn't stop following me around.

472
00:32:45,213 --> 00:32:47,590
What? I already paid you.

473
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:50,718
It's not New York. It's Washington D.C.

474
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,095
It's New York.

475
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:54,722
-Then should we ask him?
-Sure.

476
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:57,684
What would he know?

477
00:33:00,561 --> 00:33:01,646
Later on,

478
00:33:02,438 --> 00:33:04,732
I couldn't bear to live
because of that noise.

479
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:09,779
Is that why you killed
Ms. Han Geum-ok, too?

480
00:33:10,363 --> 00:33:13,658
If he doesn't like me,
why would he lend me his umbrella?

481
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:16,577
I don't get why I always
end up with jerks.

482
00:33:16,661 --> 00:33:17,745
That crazy bitch.

483
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:22,083
She treated me like a jerk
only because I let her use my umbrella.

484
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:24,085
QUICK DELIVERY

485
00:33:24,168 --> 00:33:25,920
That Chinese restaurant delivery guy?

486
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:28,548
I give them business,
and what does he say?

487
00:33:29,841 --> 00:33:33,011
You should've made instant noodles.
Why did you order in this weather?

488
00:33:34,887 --> 00:33:36,305
And you only ordered one bowl.

489
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:41,352
Joker was

490
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,606
a monster created
because of his sense of inferiority.

491
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:47,817
Those ignorant idiots

492
00:33:48,901 --> 00:33:50,570
keep behaving like a joke.

493
00:33:54,699 --> 00:33:55,783
What about Hyang-mi?

494
00:33:57,326 --> 00:33:58,911
Why did you kill Ms. Choi Hyang-mi?

495
00:34:03,791 --> 00:34:05,043
That's because

496
00:34:06,085 --> 00:34:07,754
I thought she was the other bitch.

497
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:11,758
Dongbaek.

498
00:34:14,927 --> 00:34:17,221
FISHING FESTIVAL

499
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:19,849
So why did she have to deliver it?

500
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:22,226
She was even wearing Dongbaek's bracelet.

501
00:34:30,026 --> 00:34:33,905
Did you kill her at the fishing hole
and take her to the lake after that?

502
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:43,498
Yong-sik, if you throw a dead body
in a fishing hole,

503
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:46,042
it'll rise up in just two days.

504
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:07,063
You know you can get scratched
when you throw a net, right?

505
00:35:08,564 --> 00:35:10,316
I got scratched throwing her in there.

506
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:17,115
I should have
pulled out her nails, darn it.

507
00:35:21,828 --> 00:35:22,870
Dongbaek...

508
00:35:23,955 --> 00:35:25,123
Why did you

509
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:27,834
try to kill Dongbaek?

510
00:35:28,751 --> 00:35:30,711
She keeps on messing with me.

511
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:33,422
She keeps getting on my nerves.

512
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:38,719
We got him.

513
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:40,471
He's good.

514
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:42,974
We should use him as a hired hand.

515
00:35:45,685 --> 00:35:47,937
Just let me see him, will you?

516
00:35:48,521 --> 00:35:51,899
Hey, man. Do you know
why detectives get a leeway?

517
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,110
-There are reasons--
-Hey, wait.

518
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:58,573
Were you good friends
with Park Seok-yong's son?

519
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:01,033
It's called establishing rapport.

520
00:36:01,117 --> 00:36:04,537
It's a way of making them confess
by earning their trust and friendship.

521
00:36:04,620 --> 00:36:06,038
But you've known him as a kid.

522
00:36:06,164 --> 00:36:09,041
I mean, he's your friend's father,
so you have a ground already.

523
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:13,629
On top of that, even murderers get
quite attached to their own kids.

524
00:36:13,963 --> 00:36:15,673
That's what you're after.

