779
00:54:55,125 --> 00:54:56,584
tell them it's Dongbaek.

780
00:54:57,544 --> 00:54:59,087
Just tell them your name and age.

781
00:55:01,256 --> 00:55:03,341
And if they ask you your mom's name,

782
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:05,468
tell them you don't know.

783
00:55:08,430 --> 00:55:10,265
You have to do as I say, okay?

784
00:55:11,516 --> 00:55:12,600
You fool.

785
00:55:13,310 --> 00:55:15,854
You should've remembered
what I asked you to do.

786
00:55:16,563 --> 00:55:18,356
That's how you'll be able to live here.

787
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:21,901
I'll come back with a lot of money.

788
00:55:22,861 --> 00:55:25,196
So just wait here for one year, okay?

789
00:55:26,948 --> 00:55:27,991
Wait for me.

790
00:55:28,742 --> 00:55:30,660
You understand what I mean, right?

791
00:55:41,129 --> 00:55:43,882
I was a mother who had left her daughter
at an orphanage,

792
00:55:45,342 --> 00:55:47,010
and there was nothing I couldn't do.

793
00:55:47,635 --> 00:55:50,388
Hey, get out of here
if you're going to stay quiet.

794
00:55:50,930 --> 00:55:52,098
Just leave!

795
00:55:52,807 --> 00:55:55,518
If you sit there with your mouth zipped
and looking all sad,

796
00:55:55,643 --> 00:55:57,312
who would come here to drink?

797
00:55:57,395 --> 00:55:59,606
At least smile or sing.

798
00:56:02,233 --> 00:56:05,236
Hey, get out of here.
Just leave, you bitch!

799
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:08,573
My gosh, how did I end up
with a girl like you?

800
00:56:09,199 --> 00:56:12,702
Don't forget to give me the payment
I gave you in advance, okay?

801
00:56:13,078 --> 00:56:14,913
My gosh, what an annoying bitch.

802
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:39,020
I saw the pink dress

803
00:56:39,604 --> 00:56:43,691
Fluttering in the spring wind

804
00:56:46,694 --> 00:56:47,904
Today, like any other day

805
00:56:50,281 --> 00:56:52,951
I chew on my coat string

806
00:56:53,952 --> 00:56:57,247
And head to the Village Shrine
Where the swallows visit

807
00:57:00,834 --> 00:57:06,506
When the flowers bloom, I smile with them

808
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:08,591
The moment I left you at the orphanage

809
00:57:09,759 --> 00:57:12,637
and picked up that chopstick at that bar,

810
00:57:13,430 --> 00:57:16,474
-And I cry with them
-I was no longer the same Jo Jeong-suk.

811
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:23,064
As we make a promise to each other

812
00:57:24,357 --> 00:57:30,029
The spring day slowly leaves

813
00:57:30,780 --> 00:57:34,701
That bitch ran away
as soon as she gathered all our money.

814
00:57:34,993 --> 00:57:38,037
All I ever wanted to do was get you back.

815
00:57:38,121 --> 00:57:39,581
What's with her?

816
00:57:39,747 --> 00:57:41,791
My gosh, she really is a tough one.

817
00:57:41,958 --> 00:57:43,626
-My gosh.
-There's nothing to take.

818
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:47,589
Girls' clothes
aren't even worth that much money.

819
00:57:47,672 --> 00:57:48,798
Why would you take them?

820
00:57:49,215 --> 00:57:50,675
-My gosh.
-She's unbelievable.

821
00:57:50,758 --> 00:57:52,760
But poverty was like a monkfish.

822
00:57:53,178 --> 00:57:56,181
The more I wanted to get rid of it,
the more it clung onto me.

823
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:00,602
I could've just ended it
by killing myself,

824
00:58:01,186 --> 00:58:04,147
but I couldn't stand not seeing you,
so I went to get you back.

825
00:58:05,815 --> 00:58:07,942
Dongbaek went to L.A.

826
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:11,154
"L.A."?

827
00:58:12,739 --> 00:58:14,782
Why would she go to L.A.?

828
00:58:15,825 --> 00:58:18,077
Her foster father is a professor
in theology.

829
00:58:18,161 --> 00:58:19,996
And he emigrated to the States with her.

830
00:58:20,288 --> 00:58:23,791
He and his wife are both good people
who care a lot about people's welfare.

831
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,711
Dongbaek got really lucky--

832
00:58:26,794 --> 00:58:28,588
How can you call that lucky?

833
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:30,590
Why...

834
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:31,716
Why...

835
00:58:31,799 --> 00:58:35,887
Why would you send my daughter away
without asking for my permission?

836
00:58:36,471 --> 00:58:37,847
-I'm sorry, ma'am.
-Why...

837
00:58:37,931 --> 00:58:38,932
But,

838
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:42,810
how could we ask you for permission?
We don't even know you.

839
00:58:43,311 --> 00:58:44,646
You're the one

840
00:58:45,396 --> 00:58:46,731
who left her here.

841
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:49,275
This isn't a day-care center, you know.

842
00:58:52,237 --> 00:58:55,949
You should think of your daughter
rather than yourself.

843
00:58:59,744 --> 00:59:01,538
How did she look when she left?

844
00:59:03,581 --> 00:59:06,793
Was she happy that she was
getting adopted by a rich family?

845
00:59:07,377 --> 00:59:09,003
She asked me something.

846
00:59:12,131 --> 00:59:14,259
-I have a question.
-Yes?

847
00:59:15,260 --> 00:59:17,053
Can people ride airplanes

848
00:59:18,012 --> 00:59:20,181
even though they can't ride taxis?

849
00:59:41,536 --> 00:59:43,830
My gosh, your food is the best.

850
00:59:44,831 --> 00:59:47,292
What motivated you
to do something like that?

851
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:49,627
-Let's watch something else.
-No, just leave it.

852
00:59:49,711 --> 00:59:53,965
I saw a little girl
at an orphanage one day,

853
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:55,883
and I couldn't stop thinking of her.

854
00:59:57,093 --> 00:59:59,304
And is she really...

855
00:59:59,387 --> 01:00:03,016
Yes, she's become an attorney
and a human rights activist

856
01:00:03,099 --> 01:00:05,977
who works and travels
all around the world.

857
01:00:06,894 --> 01:00:09,063
It's like a miracle to us.

858
01:00:16,112 --> 01:00:17,196
Back then,

859
01:00:18,197 --> 01:00:22,327
I thought I had made the right choice
of having abandoned you.

860
01:00:25,455 --> 01:00:26,706
I must've startled you.

861
01:00:30,168 --> 01:00:34,881
I bought this for 420,000 won
at a department store.

862
01:00:36,341 --> 01:00:37,717
I noticed that you like hats.

863
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:42,013
Here.

864
01:00:43,097 --> 01:00:47,185
I'm not here to ask you for anything.

865
01:00:48,770 --> 01:00:50,730
I just feel really grateful.

866
01:00:51,981 --> 01:00:54,859
And I thought I should do something
to show you my gratitude.

867
01:00:57,278 --> 01:00:58,655
If I could have things my way,

868
01:01:00,615 --> 01:01:03,159
I'd even give you ten years of my life.

869
01:01:04,118 --> 01:01:06,329
But there's not much I can give you.

870
01:01:10,041 --> 01:01:11,626
Would you like to meet her?

871
01:01:15,213 --> 01:01:18,424
My daughter wishes to see you.

872
01:01:24,180 --> 01:01:27,517
Dongbaek.

873
01:01:28,142 --> 01:01:29,435
Dongbaek.

874
01:01:32,105 --> 01:01:35,400
How could you forget your own name?

875
01:01:42,365 --> 01:01:43,199
Ma'am.

876
01:01:46,869 --> 01:01:48,746
Are you going to look for your daughter?

877
01:01:50,832 --> 01:01:54,752
I feel too shameless to do that
at this point.

878
01:01:56,963 --> 01:01:59,590
Are you just going to hope
that she's doing well somewhere?

879
01:02:01,759 --> 01:02:03,386
I really don't know what to say.

880
01:02:04,429 --> 01:02:06,305
Even if she was lucky and got adopted,

881
01:02:07,056 --> 01:02:09,267
every day would've
felt like a test for her.

882
01:02:10,309 --> 01:02:13,271
Other people are loved by their parents
like it's a natural thing,

883
01:02:13,855 --> 01:02:16,607
but girls like me
need to work hard for it.

884
01:02:18,609 --> 01:02:20,653
The fact that I was abandoned
by my own mother

885
01:02:22,905 --> 01:02:26,159
always made me lose my confidence
and feel insecure.

886
01:02:28,995 --> 01:02:31,330
I tried so hard to be loved
every single day.

887
01:02:32,457 --> 01:02:33,624
Because if I didn't,

888
01:02:34,542 --> 01:02:36,878
I knew I'd get sent back
just like your daughter.

889
01:02:45,636 --> 01:02:48,181
I couldn't help but wonder
why an adorable girl like you

890
01:02:49,182 --> 01:02:51,267
got sent back to the orphanage.

891
01:02:54,187 --> 01:02:55,688
Please don't ask me that.

892
01:02:56,731 --> 01:02:59,609
I'm trying to find my daughter,

893
01:03:00,151 --> 01:03:02,153
so I can't help but wonder why.

894
01:03:03,362 --> 01:03:06,240
Why did you send back
the first girl you adopted?

895
01:03:07,283 --> 01:03:08,367
It just happened.

896
01:03:13,289 --> 01:03:17,835
She had a dark side to her,
so I asked her some questions.

897
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:21,798
And it turns out
that she was raised at a nightclub.

898
01:03:22,590 --> 01:03:24,467
I think her mom used to work there.

899
01:03:26,594 --> 01:03:28,179
It just made me feel uneasy.

900
01:03:28,679 --> 01:03:30,848
They say girls end up
just like their mothers.

901
01:03:33,267 --> 01:03:36,270
Our daughter, Mi-yeon,
is a very smart girl.

902
01:03:36,354 --> 01:03:38,397
So I'm guessing her parents were
also smart.

903
01:03:39,106 --> 01:03:40,149
But she was different.

904
01:03:41,192 --> 01:03:43,694
The apple really doesn't fall
far from the tree.

905
01:03:47,573 --> 01:03:48,407
My goodness!

906
01:03:48,950 --> 01:03:50,409
That damn bitch.

907
01:03:50,785 --> 01:03:53,371
Why would Dongbaek end up like me?

908
01:03:53,996 --> 01:03:55,039
Why?

909
01:03:57,834 --> 01:03:58,876
Why would that happen?

910
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:07,760
But when I finally found you,

911
01:04:07,844 --> 01:04:09,303
-There you go.
-you were...

912
01:04:09,637 --> 01:04:11,848
We're here!

913
01:04:11,931 --> 01:04:13,808
-You were really running a bar
-Let's go.

914
01:04:14,600 --> 01:04:16,060
as a single mother.

915
01:04:17,270 --> 01:04:19,814
It really seemed as though
you had ended up just like me.

916
01:04:20,439 --> 01:04:22,275
And that really broke my heart.

917
01:04:29,198 --> 01:04:30,867
Aren't you going to talk to me?

918
01:04:31,200 --> 01:04:32,034
Come on.

919
01:04:32,910 --> 01:04:33,870
Seriously?

920
01:04:33,953 --> 01:04:36,914
-But once I took a close look...
-Do you like Pil-gu that much?

921
01:04:36,998 --> 01:04:40,793
-You'll know once you have a kid.
-You were smiling.

922
01:04:41,836 --> 01:04:43,713
-Sing louder.
-I saw you smiling.

923
01:04:45,673 --> 01:04:47,258
You weren't like me.

924
01:04:49,010 --> 01:04:51,637
I wanted to cook all the meals
I never got to cook for you.

925
01:04:52,221 --> 01:04:54,557
And I wanted to console and comfort you.

926
01:04:57,435 --> 01:05:00,354
But you were the one who embraced me.

927
01:05:02,231 --> 01:05:04,066
You gave me

928
01:05:04,400 --> 01:05:06,027
so much warmth.

929
01:05:09,906 --> 01:05:13,743
The reason I'm telling you all this

930
01:05:15,620 --> 01:05:17,330
isn't because I want to be forgiven.

931
01:05:18,581 --> 01:05:20,499
It's because I want you to know something.

932
01:05:35,681 --> 01:05:36,724
Dongbaek.

933
01:05:38,142 --> 01:05:39,518
Don't you want to see her?

934
01:05:45,691 --> 01:05:46,901
Dongbaek.

935
01:05:48,277 --> 01:05:51,113
There was not a single person
who didn't love you.

936
01:05:52,698 --> 01:05:55,159
Forget the seven-year-old
who once got abandoned.

937
01:05:56,869 --> 01:06:00,122
Don't think you lack confidence,
and don't feel intimidated.

938
01:06:00,748 --> 01:06:02,750
Live your life to the fullest.

939
01:06:05,002 --> 01:06:06,963
It wasn't just seven years
and three months.

940
01:06:08,464 --> 01:06:10,633
Throughout the past 34 years...

941
01:06:20,601 --> 01:06:25,481
I loved you every single day.

942
01:06:41,539 --> 01:06:42,581
Mom.

943
01:06:50,256 --> 01:06:51,298
Mom.

944
01:07:03,561 --> 01:07:04,603
Mom.

945
01:07:06,522 --> 01:07:07,565
Mom.

946
01:07:18,200 --> 01:07:21,537
She needs to stop telling me
she'll give me her kidney

947
01:07:22,246 --> 01:07:23,748
so I can stay for longer.

948
01:07:35,426 --> 01:07:36,302
Then how about you?

949
01:07:37,803 --> 01:07:40,014
How was your 7 years
and 3 months with me?

950
01:07:41,390 --> 01:07:42,266
Me?

951
01:07:44,685 --> 01:07:46,270
How was it?

952
01:07:48,105 --> 01:07:49,273
It felt like I was

953
01:07:51,984 --> 01:07:53,652
getting my installment savings back.

954
01:07:55,446 --> 01:07:56,489
"Installment savings"?

955
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:01,327
I've lived

956
01:08:03,954 --> 01:08:05,998
a very difficult life.

957
01:08:09,043 --> 01:08:10,753
It was so tiring.

958
01:08:12,463 --> 01:08:13,714
Life felt like

959
01:08:15,591 --> 01:08:17,384
a punishment to me.

960
01:08:20,554 --> 01:08:22,932
But after I got to spend
three more months with you,

961
01:08:28,062 --> 01:08:30,231
I realized that I had stayed alive

962
01:08:32,233 --> 01:08:35,444
just so I could finally see you again.

963
01:08:42,243 --> 01:08:45,287
It made up for all the difficult days
I had to go through.

964
01:08:48,040 --> 01:08:49,542
It wasn't good enough for me.

965
01:08:50,584 --> 01:08:52,002
But I guess it was for you.

966
01:09:03,180 --> 01:09:04,974
I guess it was only good enough for me.

967
01:09:49,268 --> 01:09:51,145
Subtitle translation by Hye-lim Park

